chest.Descriptions: Lie on the floor with either two dumbbells or two kettlebells on your hand. Press one arm at a time, while the other hand is stationary. Lower your pressing hand until either your elbow or triceps touches the floor. Press the weight back up and repeat with the other hand.

Lie flat on the bench, Lift the bar out of the rack straight above your chest with arms locked. Come down slowly until the bar touches the middle of your chest. After a brief pause push the bar straight up while breathing out.

Lie flat on the bench, Lift the bar out of the rack straight above your chest with arms locked. Come down slowly until the bar is about 1 inch from your neck. After a brief pause push the bar straight up while breathing out.

Sit down either on the floor or a bench, have your back straight and chest up. Place your hand on the back of your hand. Have someone or partner place their hands on your elbows and pull your elbows back until there's a stretch in your chest. Hold it for a few secoonds and bring your elbows in. Relax and repeat.

Attach resistence bands on two ends of the barbell. Lie flat on the bench, Lift the bar out of the rack straight above your chest with arms locked. Come down slowly until the bar touches the middle of your chest. After a brief pause push the bar straight up while breathing out.

Place a dumbbell standing up on a flat bench. Lie down perpendicular to the bench with only your shoulders lying on the surface and watch out for the dumbbell on the bench. hold on to the dumbbell with both palms facing toward the sky. The starting position should be arms straight with dumbbell directly on top of your chest. Keep your arms locked in the bent arm position and low the weight behind your head. Once you feel a stretch on the chest, bring the weight back to starting postion and repeat.

Set up the dual pulleys to chest height and select a weight that is challanging yet able to maintain good form. Hold onto the handles facing away from the pulley system and about a foot or two in front of it. Position the upper arms perpendicular with shoulder blades together. While kepping the body stationary, press the handles forward by extending your elbows. Once your elbows are fully extended, return back to the position before.

chest.Exercise: chest and front of shoulder stretch
chest.Descriptions: Wrap a resistance band around a pull up bar. Stand with your legs together. Place one side of your hand around a resistance band. Turn your body slowly to the opposite side of whichever hand is holding onto the band. Once you feel a stretch, return back to starting position and repeat with the other hand.

Begin in a kneeling position holding a medicine ball with both hands tightly into the chest. Push the ball as far as possible by exploding forward and outward with the hips. Finish the movement by falling forward and catching youself with your hands.

Begin in running position with knees bent, hips back and back flat. Hold the medicine ball near your legs. While taking the first step draw the medicine ball into your chest. Explosively push the ball forward as you take the second step. immediately sprint forward as you release the ball.

Wrap an exercise band around a stationary post. grab the handles on the band and step forward, opposite of the post. Raise your arms to the sides, parallel to the floor, as well as perpendicular to your torso. Your palms should be facing forward. While keeping straight arms, bring them across your chest until you feel contraction on your pecs. Return to starting position slowly and repeat.
